From: Rob Woolley <rob.woolley@windriver.com>
Subject: cmake: kconfig: respect an externally provided CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE

Build systems such as Yocto/OpenEmbedded pass their own cross toolchain
via -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE. Force-overriding it from the board config
makes subprojects that forward CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE (e.g. the
Micro-XRCE-DDS-Client ExternalProject) pick PX4's bare-triple toolchain
without the distro sysroot. Only apply the board toolchain as a default.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [needs discussion upstream first]

Signed-off-by: Rob Woolley <rob.woolley@windriver.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/cmake/kconfig.cmake b/cmake/kconfig.cmake
index 741e5e85bf..854d2e9827 100644
--- a/cmake/kconfig.cmake
+++ b/cmake/kconfig.cmake
@@ -297,7 +297,12 @@ if(EXISTS ${BOARD_DEFCONFIG})
 		set(CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR ${ARCHITECTURE} CACHE INTERNAL "system processor" FORCE)
 	endif()
 
-	if(TOOLCHAIN)
+	# Don't override a toolchain file provided on the command line (e.g. by a
+	# distribution build system such as Yocto/OpenEmbedded, which passes its own
+	# cross toolchain via -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE). The board toolchain is only a
+	# default; forcing it here would also make subprojects that forward
+	# CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE pick the wrong compilers and sysroot.
+	if(TOOLCHAIN AND NOT CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE)
 		set(CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE Toolchain-${TOOLCHAIN} CACHE INTERNAL "toolchain file" FORCE)
 	endif()
 
